<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE6683B441830CEBB8DFA52" box="[325,502,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">Tinodes radona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Radon Springs in the NT and three sites in North Queensland (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE6683B447730E2BBB3F98E" author="Neboiss, A." box="[298,456,1513,1539]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" pagination="83 - 86" refId="ref15404" refString="Neboiss, A. (1990) The family Psychomyiidae (Trichoptera) re-established in Australia. Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 83 - 86. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 1990.51.04" type="journal article" year="1990">Neboiss 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE6683B448630E2B810F989" author="Wells, A." box="[475,619,1513,1540]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" pagination="53 - 59" refId="ref15815" refString="Wells, A. (1995) Larva, pupa and notes on general biology of Tinodes radona Neboiss (Trichoptera: Psychomyiidae). The Beagle, Records of the Museums and Art Galleries of the Northern Territory, 12, 53 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 264276" type="journal article" year="1995">Wells (1995)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE6683B478B30E1B939F98E" box="[726,834,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Psychomyiidae" genus="Tinodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radona">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE6683B478B30E1B939F98E" box="[726,834,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">T. radona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae from three sites in Kakadu and Litchfield NPs. The species is recorded from a further five NT sites. A second species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE6683B469F3305BE8CF9AA" authority="Kimmins 1962" authorityName="Kimmins" authorityYear="1962" box="[962,1271,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Psychomyiidae" genus="Tinodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE6683B469F3305BE38F9AA" box="[962,1091,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">T. aberrans</emphasis>
Kimmins 1962
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from New 
<collectingCountry id="F34961BCFFE6683B4435333ABBC7F9C6" box="[360,444,1585,1611]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="19" pageNumber="302">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, has been reported from North Queensland (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE6683B46F1333ABE41F9C6" author="ABRS" box="[940,1082,1585,1611]" pageId="19" pageNumber="302" refId="ref14467" refString="ABRS (2021) Australian Faunal Directory. Trichoptera. Australian Biological Resources Study, Canberra. Available from: https: // biodiversity. org. au / afd / taxa / TRICHOPTERA (accessed 30 August 2021)" type="url" year="2021">ABRS 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
